race.comment: CALLISTEMON (8) underrated mare resuming with solid fresh figures. Raced with distinction in this grade last time in and since fitted with a searching 1150m trial placing at Kembla. Can sit off the fast tempo and pounce late. BROADWAY BOUNCER (3) at his top for this and sharp improvement is expected after disappointing last Saturday when ninth over 1600m at Newcastle in this class. Assess on his eye-catching run when fifth in the Four Pillars two-back. ALL MACHIAVELLIAN (16) faded late with the 58kg when sixth over the mile here in weaker company. Well placed over this trip and will give them something to catch on the limit. Each way. ROLLING MAGIC (1) progressive gelding who will keep improving as he gets out in trip. Will go back from the gate and be ridden for luck. BOJANGLES (17) hard fit and well placed in this easier contest. Outclassed when seven over 1300m at Newcastle last Saturday in BM94 grade. No excuses with the claim.
